<br>
From a strict utilitarian viewpoint, SCM (spell casting mastery) can't be beat, regardless of your spec or what you enjoy casting more.  Though the 1st point of MC (mental clarity) is just as useful as SCM, if not moreso.  Second point of MC is questionable, 3rd is not a good deal at all.  Those who prefer nuking and eye-candy will like SCF.<br>
<br>
Since you enjoy healing, the HA and HG skills are nice, though remember that you will heal the same on a bar of mana with SCM3, as you will with HA3 or HG3.  The difference is you will also benefit from SCM3 when not healing.  Although with HA or HG, you HP/second of healing will be slightly higher.<br>
<br>
SCR is nice, but you have to be spending a LOT of mana on buffs to justify it before taking SCM.<br>
<br>
Then there is the channeling skill (forget name).  Not too many take that one.<br>
<br>
My recommendation would be SCM3, it's just as beneficial to your healing as HA and HG, but also helps when you're not healing.  However, I'll add this one other comment.  If you want to get some class skills ASAP, do SCM3.  This takes 12 AAs to do, and that's how many AAs you need to unlock class skills.  If you are not planning on getting to class skills right away, then do MC1 (just the 1st one), then do SCM3.  That 1st point of MC is really very nice, but messes up your progression if going to class quickly.<br>
<br>
